<paragraph blockId="1.[174,1229,1779,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">
Рис. 1. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zerova &amp; Seryogina, 2014" authorityName="Zerova &amp; Seryogina" authorityYear="2014" box="[243,424,1779,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Ormyridae" genus="Ormyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askanicus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[243,424,1779,1801]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">Ormyrus askanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[429,480,1779,1801]" pageId="1" pageNumber="282" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<emphasis box="[492,527,1779,1801]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">1–5</emphasis>
) и 
<emphasis box="[558,641,1779,1801]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">O. novus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[658,693,1779,1801]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">6–9</emphasis>
): 
<emphasis box="[712,723,1779,1801]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">1</emphasis>
— самка, вид сбоку; 
<emphasis box="[932,943,1779,1801]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">2</emphasis>
— голова спереди; 
<emphasis box="[1139,1150,1779,1801]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">3</emphasis>
— усик самки; 
<emphasis box="[248,259,1806,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">4</emphasis>
— жилкование передних крыльев; 
<emphasis box="[630,641,1806,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">5</emphasis>
— метасома; 
<emphasis box="[786,797,1806,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">6</emphasis>
— самка, вид сбоку; 
<emphasis box="[1019,1030,1806,1828]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">7</emphasis>
— голова спереди; 
<emphasis box="[174,185,1832,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">8</emphasis>
— усик самки; 
<emphasis box="[343,354,1832,1854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="282">9</emphasis>
— жилкование передних крыльев.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,778]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Metasoma longer than mesosoma as 60: 35 (in profile), female gaster dorsally with longitudinal median carina on T2–T5, but carina is not sharp. Apex of the gaster is short but distinct uplifted; epipygium the same length as T6; T1 with distinct punctation, T2–T5 with shallow pits and rows of foweae, T6 with thin reticulation. All gasteral tergites without distinct pubescence; T4 dorsal with large dark-yellow spot.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,778]" box="[219,421,399,426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">M a l e unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,778]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
B i o l o g y. Reared from flower heads of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bieb." authorityName="Bieb." box="[699,1067,431,458]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Serratula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="xeranthemoides">
<emphasis box="[699,999,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Serratula xeranthemoides</emphasis>
Bieb.
</taxonomicName>
inhabited by 
<taxonomicName box="[166,304,463,490]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tephritidae</taxonomicName>
larvae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[166,1225,175,778]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
D i s c u s s i o n. 
<taxonomicName authority="Zerova &amp; Seryogina, 2014" authorityName="Zerova &amp; Seryogina" authorityYear="2014" box="[405,632,495,522]" class="Insecta" family="Ormyridae" genus="Ormyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askanicus" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[405,632,495,522]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">Ormyrus askanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[642,698,495,522]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1871" box="[844,952,495,521]" class="Insecta" family="Ormyridae" genus="Ormyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[844,952,495,521]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group (female gaster with dorsal median keel, 
<figureCitation box="[537,594,527,554]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1683,1705]" captionTargetBox="[188,1214,209,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-8@1.[170,1229,174,1631]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Ormyrus askanicus sp. n. (1–5) and O. novus (6–9): 1 — female, lateral view; 2 — head, frontal view; 3 — antenna female; 4 — forewing venation; 5 — metasoma from above; 6 — female, lateral view; 7 — head, frontal view; 8 — antenna female; 9 — forewing venation." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453177/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis box="[607,621,528,554]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">5</emphasis>
). In this group, the new species is close to 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1832" box="[1121,1225,528,554]" class="Insecta" family="Ormyridae" genus="Ormyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ormyrus</taxonomicName>
novus
</emphasis>
Zerova, 2012 (
<figureCitation box="[412,473,559,586]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[174,207,1683,1705]" captionTargetBox="[188,1214,209,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-8@1.[170,1229,174,1631]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Ormyrus askanicus sp. n. (1–5) and O. novus (6–9): 1 — female, lateral view; 2 — head, frontal view; 3 — antenna female; 4 — forewing venation; 5 — metasoma from above; 6 — female, lateral view; 7 — head, frontal view; 8 — antenna female; 9 — forewing venation." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453177" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453177/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis box="[488,502,559,585]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">6</emphasis>
) from the 
<collectingCountry box="[632,894,559,586]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">United Arab Emirates</collectingCountry>
(Zerova, Seryogina, Harten Van, 2012). The both species have oval gaster (in profile), and the apex of the gaster is short and uplifted. The peculiarities of funicular segments are also similar, but in the new species the F2–F6 are shorter. The new species can be easily distinguished from 
<emphasis box="[1011,1114,656,682]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">O. novus</emphasis>
by structure of venation with short postmarginal vein and by colour of body — bright blue green in 
<taxonomicName authority="Zerova &amp; Seryogina, 2014" authorityName="Zerova &amp; Seryogina" authorityYear="2014" box="[197,344,719,746]" class="Insecta" family="Ormyridae" genus="Ormyrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="askanicus" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis box="[197,344,719,746]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">O. askanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[351,406,719,746]" pageId="2" pageNumber="283" rank="species">sp.n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and dark green in 
<emphasis box="[628,730,720,746]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="283">O. novus</emphasis>
. Moreover the gaster by new species has a dark-yellow spot on dorsal side of T4.
</paragraph>
